parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to unexpected stopping of the vehicle, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
the steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tie rod end snaps or breaks
the vehicle stops suddenly
abnormal sounds or noises from the front end
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the vehicle vibrates or shakes
the vehicle pulls to one side
abnormal sounds or noises from the front end
and the vehicle becomes difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can cause drivers to continue driving vehicles with known safety issues, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The dealer or manufacturer is unable to perform the recall repair due to parts unavailability
the driver is forced to continue driving the vehicle with a known safety issue
and the driver experiences anxiety or fear due to the safety issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning AEB system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop or brake without warning, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also cause unnecessary wear and tear on the vehicle's brakes and other components.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes without warning
the AEB warning light flashes
the dashboard displays a warning message
the vehicle beeps or makes an audible warning sound
and the brakes may be applied abruptly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning forward collision warning system can cause the vehicle to fail to alert the driver of potential collisions, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The forward collision warning light flashes
the dashboard displays a warning message
the vehicle beeps or makes an audible warning sound
and the system may fail to alert the driver of potential collisions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including door lock and window issues, backup camera failure, and sudden braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Doors won't lock or unlock
windows won't roll up or down
backup camera displays a blue screen
sudden braking
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AEB system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden braking
warning lights on the dashboard
